Well, to outline it - people tend to take up patterns of comfort no matter if sitting in a chair or standing and those do end up in unhealthy postures. However, in a chair your whole skelette is supported by simply sitting, but if you stay up and you, let's say, rotate your hip a bit whilst supporting your weight with your elbow on the desk or something like that you will end up putting a lot of strain on your hip rotators and joints. People tend to not realize that whilst being focused.

you know... no matter if you sit wront or stand wrong - the outcome is the same and standing wrong will fuck your joints up way faster due to undampered bone friction than sitting will. The most dangerous part on wrong sitting is overstraining and overstretching your ligaments and slightly pulling joints in the neck or comparable.
